-- Aeroflot, Gazprom Neft, Gazprom May Move Today: Russian Equities Preview
-- Stephen Bierman
-- 2010-07-11T23:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/aeroflot-gazprom-neft-gazprom-may-move-today-russian-equities-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses, and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  
 The  Micex Index  of 30 stocks was up 0.27 percent to
1,324.17 at the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS
Index rose 0.25 percent to 1,359.45.  
 OAO Aeroflot  (AFLT RX): Russian Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  criticized Russia’s largest airline for not buying enough
airplanes or technology domestically. Aeroflot shares rose 3.4
percent to 61.63 in Moscow.  
 OAO Gazprom Neft  (SIBN RX): Arabtec Construction Chief
Executive Officer  Thomas Barry  said that the Russian oil company
hasn’t changed plans for the $2.7 billion 400-meter tower in
St. Petersburg even as one poll showed 72 percent of city
residents opposed it. The state-run oil producer fell 0.13
percent to 118.52 rubles.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): A project to build a liquefied
natural gas plant with Japanese partners in Russia’s far eastern
city of Vladivostok may have an annual capacity to produce up to
5 million tons of the fuel, Nikkei English News reported.
Russia’s gas export monopoly rose 1.4 percent to 154.17 in
Moscow.  
